UID:87362-1775410200-1775415600@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:Worlds Unknown: A Cosmic Investigation
DESCRIPTION:Humans have always looked to the skies.  \nThe stars have carried our maps\, inspired our myths and provoked our most enduring question: are we alone in the universe?  \nEach leap in technology extended our reach and sharpened our sight. The telescope. The spectrograph. Space-based observatories. And now\, the James Webb Space Telescope\, the most powerful eye we have ever pointed at the sky\, capable of reading the chemical signatures of atmospheres on planets orbiting distant stars. \nThis session takes us to the frontier: Hycean worlds\, temperate and ocean-covered\, with hydrogen-rich atmospheres. A possibly habitable exoplanet\, K2-18 b\, was observed recently. The first detections of carbon-bearing molecules in its atmosphere\, along with hints of a potential biomarker\, usher in a new era of astrobiology.  \nThe floor will open to audience questions after the talk. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/worlds-unknown-a-cosmic-investigation/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Science
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Thumbnail_WU.jpg
